Usage: python scrub_pg.py [INPUT_FILE] [INPUT_BUCKET_META_FILE]

Preparing input files:
INPUT_FILE - Get acting set of the PG that has to be scrubbed. Go to one of the OSDs and to the physical location of the PG (/var/lib/ceph/osd/ceph-<OSDNUM>/current).
Write the output of this command to a file and pass it as input to this scrubber.

INPUT_BUCKET_META_FILE - <To_be_filled> A file that contains bucket_id along with bucket_name

Parameters:
INPUT_FILE  	         - Input file which contains all the filenames in the PG
INPUT_BUCKET_META_FILE   - Input file that contains bucket meta

Examples:
  python scrub_pg.py filenames bucket.meta
